.SH NAME
devlink_remote_reload_actions_performed \- Update devlink on reload actions performed which are not a direct result of devlink reload call.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" devlink_remote_reload_actions_performed
.BI "(struct devlink *devlink "  ","
.BI "enum devlink_reload_limit limit "  ","
.BI "u32 actions_performed "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "devlink" 12
devlink
.IP "limit" 12
reload limit
.IP "actions_performed" 12
bitmask of actions performed
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

This should be called by a driver after performing reload actions in case it was not
a result of devlink reload call. For example fw_activate was performed as a result
of devlink reload triggered fw_activate on another host.
The motivation for this function is to keep data on reload actions performed on this
function whether it was done due to direct devlink reload call or not.
